**Floyd's cycle finding — second phase**:
After slow/fast meet inside the cycle, math shows the distance from the head to the cycle entry equals the distance from the meeting point to the cycle entry (modulo cycle length). So move one pointer back to head and step both 1 at a time; they meet at the entry.

